						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in a private house.</p>						

						<p>Kulaśēkhara (II), 1346 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damage record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1267, Pārthiva, Phālguṇa ba. 6, Mīna 19, Tuesday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1346 A.D., March 14.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers a grant of land to Aṇṇa-Oraṁbaḷi of Brahmavūru by the king while he was holding assembly in his palace <hi rend="italic">(hiriy-aramane),</hi> at <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru</hi> in the presence of his ministers and others, for maintaining a <hi rend="italic">maṭha (?)</hi></p>						

						</summary>
